Description.note:
Transcribed from container: "Don Davis, producer, and Damon Harris, and Richard/Charles (2 of 2), May 13, 1974";  

On side A, Don Davis talks about how the public hears pop music versus how a producer listens; how he picks material to produce; his inspirations; how one gets into producing; and his future plans in the business. Also on side A, starting at 29:21, Davis discusses his production role for the move Psycho; his thoughts on the creation of a Black production company; how he feels about Academy Awards; and Black success in the industry.  

On side B, Damon Harris discusses his career and family plans as a new member of the Temptations and his advice for people who want to get into the business. Also on Side B, starting at 19:26, interviewee--possibly Richard or Charles--discusses when he started doing music; upcoming tours; what artist has influenced his music; his plans for the next album; how he describes himself musically; and his opinions on new guitar artists.
